# Privileges — what each buys

| Privilege | Lets you… |
|---|---|
| `USE CATALOG` / `USE SCHEMA` | see schemas / objects |
| **`SELECT`** | read rows |
| **`MODIFY`** | INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE/MERGE + ALTER |
| `CREATE` / `CREATE TABLE` | create objects inside |
| `EXECUTE` | call a function |
| `READ/WRITE VOLUME` | read/write files |
| `BROWSE` | see metadata, **not** data |
| `APPLY TAG` | tag for governance (ABAC) |
| `ALL PRIVILEGES` | everything (sparingly) |

- **Ownership ≠ privileges** — owner can do anything incl. change grants; **one owner**; `ALTER ... OWNER TO <group>`
- Exam: `SELECT`(read) vs `MODIFY`(write) · `BROWSE`(exists) vs `SELECT`(rows)
